CIMB’s Razak Says Sri Lanka Building Stable Macro Economy

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e   a n d   A s a n t h a   S i r i m a n n e ,
-- 
2011-08-04T11:36:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/cimb-s-razak-says-sri-lanka-building-stable-macro-economy.html
Nazir Razak, chief executive officer
of  CIMB Group Holdings Bhd. (CIMB) , comments on  Sri Lanka ’s economic
prospects. He spoke to reporters in the capital Colombo today
after CIMB, Malaysia’s second-biggest lender, took a 51 percent
stake in a newly formed Sri Lankan investment banking and
corporate advisory firm.  On Sri Lanka’s economic prospects:  “We are impressed with the future for Sri Lanka and the
government’s far-sighted plans to transform the country by
building stable macroeconomic fundamentals.  ‘‘Sri Lanka is seeing a growing level of industrial and
financial activity and we believe in its economic growth
potential.’’  On CIMB’s plans in Sri Lanka:  ‘‘We will avail our clients in Southeast Asia. We will also
avail opportunities in Southeast Asia to Sri Lankan firms who
want to go international. Many of our ASEAN clients are already
significant trade partners and investors here. We also see
opportunities in infrastructure and plantations.’’  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anusha Ondaatjie in  Colombo  at 
 anushao@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
